<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARACLETE PARLAYS ZEROS INTO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paraclete High's 46-34 victory over Rosamond in a High Desert League boys' 
basketball game Tuesday night began as zero hour. 
</P>
<P>
 At the end of the first quarter: Paraclete 0, Rosamond 0. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosamond (8-11, 2-7 in league play) lost to the Spirits (9-10, 6-3) by 40 
points in their first meeting, so they slowed the pace this time. After 
Rosamond missed a shot and Paraclete missed two free throws, the Roadrunners 
held the ball for the last six minutes of the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was like a standoff in the sun, who's going to blink first," Paraclete 
Coach Andy Gavel said. "We didn't care because we had the possession arrow to 
start the second quarter." 
</P>
</TEXT>
