<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kodak Profit Down 33%: The Rochester, N.Y.-based company said it earned $201 
million in the fourth quarter, a significant drop from a year ago when profit 
was boosted by an asset sale.Profit for the quarter ended Dec. 31 amounted to 
61 cents a share. A year ago, Eastman Kodak Co. earned $299 million, or 92 
cents a share, in the same period. Revenue was $4.54 billion, down 2% from 
$4.65 billion a year ago. The company's fourth-quarter 1992 results were lifted 
23 cents a share from the sale of Eastman Kodak Credit Corp. and other 
investments. Without that boost, the company's latest profit was 11.5% below 
the year-ago quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
