<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: RAIN BRINGS FOOD TO TROUT, TROUT TO ANGLERS AT IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Last week's rain is being credited with triggering a steady bite of rainbow 
and German brown trout at Irvine Lake. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials there said runoff from the rain carried worms, so those using 
nightcrawlers and red worms had little trouble catching their five-fish limits. 
The largest fish of the week, a 7 1/2-pound rainbow trout, was caught by Craig 
Schlisct of Glendora. 
</P>
</TEXT>
