<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; PHILMAN, EDISON UPSET MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marie Philman had 30 points to help Edison to a 66-59 upset of Marina, the 
fifth-ranked team in Orange County, in a Sunset League girls' basketball game 
Tuesday at Marina. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss stopped Marina's 25-game home winning streak and also dropped the 
Vikings (16-6, 9-2) into a first-place tie with Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
 Philman, a sophomore forward, set an Edison single-game record by making 16 
free throws. She made 11 of 13 free throws in the fourth quarter. Edison (14-8, 
5-6) trailed, 28-25, at the half, but the Chargers increased their defensive 
pressure and outscored Marina 23-13 in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sunset League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 58, Rosary 33 -- Farrah Magee had 16 points and Jennifer Tuiolosega 
