<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Yolanda Hearvey 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Forward 
</P>
<P>
 Hearvey, a 6-foot-1 sophomore from Magnolia High, shows amazing versatility 
for the Chargers. As expected, she leads the team with 53 blocked shots.But 
unexpectedly she tops the team in steals with 67. She is also averaging three 
assists. Hearvey had 15 points, 10 rebounds, seven steals and four assists as 
the Chargers lost to Riverside, 62-60. She then scored 19 points as Cypress 
beat Rancho Santiago, 82-31, Friday. She has 511 rebounds in her career, 
second-best in Cypress history after Joyce Rice (1979-81), who had 557. Other 
notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Katie Miner, Golden West, had 22 points and 10 rebounds as the Rustlers beat 
Riverside, 71-70. 
</P>
<P>
 * LeAnn Kazmer, Orange Coast, made 12 of 14 shots from the field, scoring 26 
points in the Pirates' 82-50 victory over Rancho Santiago. 
