<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; COUNTY TO PURCHASE SITE FOR HEALTH CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TINA DAUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Moving forward after months of delays, the Ventura County Board of Supervisors 
on Tuesday approved an agreement to purchase a building owned by Texaco for the 
new site of the west Ventura public health clinic. 
</P>
<P>
 Convinced that environmental concerns at the site would be addressed, the 
supervisors voted unanimously to purchase the building at 133 W. Santa Clara 
St. for $1.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Public works officials told the board on Tuesday that after extensive 
negotiations Texaco agreed to pay to remove asbestos ceiling tiles and clean up 
soil contamination from underground fuel tanks at the site. 
</P>
<P>
 The building will serve as the new site for the West Ventura Family Care 
Clinic, now operating in tight quarters at 110 N. Olive St. in Ventura. TINA 
DAUNT 
</P>
</TEXT>
