<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRAISE FOR STAFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I want to publicly thank all of the employees, physicians and auxiliary 
members who gave so generously of themselves Monday, Jan. 17, following the 
earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 It is a true testimony of commitment and selflessness when those you work with 
leave their families and homes to come to the aid of those in need. 
</P>
<P>
 We were fortunate. The hospital suffered no structural damage. Our emergency 
generators kicked in immediately. There was no panic. Our staff reacted to the 
disaster in the most professional way. 
</P>
<P>
 Our emergency room saw five times the number of patients as seen on a typical 
Monday. Physicians in all specialties simply showed up. Not one needed 
physician or employee was called in to help -- they were already here. 
</P>
<P>
 K.D. JUSTYN 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake Village 
</P>
<P>
 K.D. Justyn is managing director of the Westlake Medical Center.  
</P>
