<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SOUTH-CENTRAL; TIP FROM 
HOMELESS MAN LEADS TO STOLEN COMPUTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A tip from a homeless man led police Tuesday to a house in South-Central Los 
Angeles where about $300,000 worth of stolen computer monitors were found. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers found the monitors throughout the house and in the back yard in the 
300 block of West 88th Place, said Los Angeles Police Detective Ray Allen.The 
monitors apparently were stolen from a truck parked near Indiana Street and 
Olympic Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 A man pushing a shopping cart became suspicious when he saw what he thought 
was a large number of TV sets in the back yard, so he notified police. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe that the thieves unloaded the truck and ditched it at 98th 
Street and Avalon Boulevard, where it was found by officers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
