<TEXT>
<P>
 The following hot lines operated by the Los Angeles Department of Building and 
Safety have been set up for information related to earthquake damage 
inspections: 
</P>
<P>
 * For first inspections of earthquake-damaged buildings not yet evaluated by 
Building and Safety: (800) 655-4095  
</P>
<P>
 * For questions or disputes about the red, yellow, or green tags posted on 
buildings after emergency inspections by Building and Safety teams: (800) 
890-0223.Information is also available to help residents interpret when 
structures are safe to enter or occupy.  
</P>
<P>
 * For questions about dwellings evaluated as unsafe to occupy, as indicated by 
a red or yellow tag: (800) 664-2489. Information is also available on 
procedures for obtaining an emergency re-entry for limited retrieval of 
possessions. 
