<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 'I STILL 
LOVE L.A.' STICKERS TO BENEFIT SALVATION ARMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Korean American Chamber of Commerce of Los Angeles will sell bumper 
stickers with a morale-boosting message to raise the spirits of 
disaster-ravaged Angelenos while raising money for victims.  
</P>
<P>
 The stickers pay tribute to the indomitable spirit of those who have overcome 
all manner of disasters in recent years and stayed in the area, said chamber 
executive director Harrison Kim. 
</P>
<P>
 The stickers carry the message, "After the Riot, Floods, Fires and 
Earthquakes, I Still Love L.A." They will sell for $1 apiece, with proceeds 
going to the Salvation Army's Operation We Care program, Kim said. The stickers 
will be sold through the mail and, if all goes well, at chain convenience 
stores and independent businesses, Kim said.  
</P>
<P>
 Stickers are available from the Korean American Chamber of Commerce of Los 
Angeles, 3350 Wilshire Blvd., Suite. 660, Los Angeles 90010. 
</P>
<P>
 Checks for money orders should be made out to "I Still Love L.A." and orders 
of fewer than 20 should include a stamped, self-addressed envelope. For orders 
of 20 or more, Kim said, the chamber will pay postage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
