<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAMS' JACKSON TO DISCUSS JOB WITH NEW FALCON COACH JONES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ram receivers coach Milt Jackson will meet with the Atlanta Falcons today to 
discuss taking a similar position with the staff of new Coach June Jones. 
</P>
<P>
 Jackson said the Rams granted the Falcons permission to talk to him.His 
contract with the Rams expires in February. 
</P>
<P>
 Jackson flew to Atlanta on Tuesday and will interview today with Jones and 
other team officials. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're still in the talking stage," Jackson said. "We haven't reached a verbal 
agreement, but I know they are interested in hiring me." 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, promoted from offensive coordinator to head coach on Jan. 24, didn't 
retain receivers coach Jimmy Robinson from the staff of former head coach Jerry 
Glanville. 
</P>
<P>
 Jackson joined Ram Coach Chuck Knox's staff for the 1992 season. He coached 
wide receivers at Indianapolis from 1989-91 and from 1986-88 at Houston, where 
he worked with Jones. 
</P>
<P>
 "June and I have been good friends for a long time," Jackson said. MIKE 
REILLEY 
</P>
