<HEADLINE>
<P>
BURBANK REPORTEDLY NEAR HIRING HAZELTON AS FOOTBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANA HADDAD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montclair Prep assistant John Hazelton is the overwhelming choice to be named 
football coach at Burbank High, a Burbank district official said Tuesday. 
Hazelton and two other finalists will be interviewed today by a selection 
committee. 
</P>
<P>
 The other candidates to replace Dave Kemp as coach are Glendale College 
assistant Robert Dos Remedios and St. Genevieve Coach Richard Fong. 
</P>
<P>
 But the official, who wished to remain anonymous, said Hazelton is the 
favorite to turn the Bulldogs around from their 2-8 record in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 "Hazelton will go 7-3 next year," he said. "Hazelton has won CIF 
championships. We're serious about building athletics here. It's important to 
us to turn this thing around." 
</P>
<P>
 Hazelton has served two stints at Montclair Prep, from 1982-85 and from 1989 
to the present. His only head coaching job lasted one season at Banning in 
1987. The Pilots were 6-4 and reached the quarterfinals of the City Section 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 "People in the community, boosters and people on the inside are telling me I 
should be the guy," Hazelton said. "There's a tremendous amount of support." 
</P>
</TEXT>
