<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRABUCO HILLS' CERVANTES PICKS USC; VEDDER OF LAGUNA HILLS SELECTS BU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Cervantes of Trabuco Hills has made an oral commitment to USC and 
quarterback Justin Vedder of Laguna Hills committed to Boston University. 
</P>
<P>
 Cervantes, a 6-foot-4, 215-pound defensive lineman, earned All-Southern 
Section Division VIII honors and helped the Mustangs win the Division VIII 
championship last season.He also was named All-Pacific Coast League at tight 
end. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm excited," Cervantes said. "They said I'm too small to play Division I 
line, but they like my speed, so I'm moving to outside linebacker." 
</P>
<P>
 Cervantes, who plays first base for Trabuco Hills and was a first-team 
All-Pacific Coast League selection last year, will also play baseball for the 
Trojans. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills Coach Steve Bresnahan said Vedder, a 6-1, 180-pound senior, chose 
Boston University, a Division I-AA school, over Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
 Vedder started three seasons at Laguna Hills and in 1991 helped the Hawks win 
their first Southern Section football championship. He completed 55% of his 
passes for 2,129 yards and 20 touchdowns last season and also rushed for four 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hawks reached the Division VIII semifinals last season, where they lost to 
eventual champion Trabuco Hills. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
