<P>
 Nation's Manufacturing Growth Surges: The managers who do the buying for the 
nation's factories reported the healthiest manufacturing growth in 5 1/2 years 
in January, but their monthly assessment carried a troublesome warning of 
higher inflation. The National Assn. of Purchasing Management's monthly survey 
on the economy was unexpectedly strong and bolstered other evidence that the 
economic expansion in the final three months of 1993 carried over into 1994. 
The survey also indicates higher price increases filtering down to consumers in 
coming months, perhaps heralding an end to the tame inflation that has 
characterized the recovery from the 1990-91 recession. 
