<TEXT>
<P>
 Russian Industrial Output Plummets: The record 25.5% decline in January 
compared to a year earlier was reported by the State Statistics Committee in 
Moscow, according to the Interfax news agency. Industrial output fell 18% in 
1993 and 16% in 1992. Russia's new government, dominated by conservative 
ministers with close links to industry, hopes to support production with 
growth-oriented policies, including cheap loans to agriculture and higher state 
subsidies. 
