Center for Economic Research, also told restaurant owners and operators that 
the Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake won't have a dramatic effect on revenue at 
most Orange County restaurants. Doti based that statement on the fact that the 
1989 Loma Prieta earthquake did relatively little damage to sales at 
restaurants located away from that temblor's epicenter. 
