<P>
TACO BELL TO AID VICTIMS' CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Taco Bell said Tuesday it has organized a charitable fund to aid in the 
education of the children whose parents were killed at one of the chain's 
restaurants in Clarksville, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
 The Clarksville Children's Memorial Fund is accepting donations in care of 
First American National Bank, P.O. Box 508, Clarksville, Tenn. 37041-0508. 
</P>
<P>
 Taco Bell said it would donate $5,000 per child to the fund. The company is 
also preparing to pay funeral expenses, and it has arranged for counseling for 
the victims' families and co-workers. 
</P>
<P>
 The four workers slain Sunday were Patricia Mae Price, 28; Angela Wyatt and 
Kevin Campbell, both 22, and Marsha Klopp, 24. Campbell, the married father of 
a 2-week-old girl, was expecting a promotion to assistant manager. Klopp, an 
assistant manager, also was married with three children. Price had five 
children and had recently moved to Clarksville with her husband. 
</P>
<P>
 The four victims were found dead Sunday morning by the restaurant manager 
arriving to open for business. Two had been shot in the head execution-style, 
authorities said. The restaurant's safe was open and cash register drawers were 
empty. 
</P>
